<p>Across all of it, three rules matter most for a Dachshund: <strong>keep your pup lean</strong>, because excess weight is the one big IVDD risk factor you control and the habit is set young; <strong>feed a balanced complete food</strong> (don't add calcium supplements unless your vet says so) with omega-3 for the joints; and <strong>protect the back day to day</strong> — ramps not jumps, two-handed lifts, gentle low-impact exercise while the skeleton matures. Because the breed is genuinely prone to spinal disease, any sign of back pain, reluctance to jump or walk, wobbliness or dragging paws warrants a prompt vet visit — these are not things to wait out.</p>

